<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-22T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-22T14:00:00-05:00" n="14" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d14">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">859A.20/185: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister to the Norwegian Government in Exile</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-22T21:00:00+02:00">May 22,
                                    1942—9 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received May 22—7:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Norwegian Series No. 9. Norwegian Government accepts in principle
                            proposal contained in your 9, May 20, 9 p.m.</p>
                        <p>It desires that details of arrangement be embodied in a formal millitary
                            agreement which it hopes may be concluded at an early date.</p>
                        <pb facs="0017" n="11" xml:id="pg_11"/>
                        <p>Norwegian Government also desires that negotiations regarding these
                            details be carried out in agreement with the British military thorities.
                            This is necessary in order to avoid any conflict with military
                            agreements with the British which regulate strength of Norwegian forces
                            in different areas.</p>
                        <closer>[<signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Biddle</hi>
                            </signed>]</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>